Class MeshEntity2

java.lang.Object
camzup.core.Entity
camzup.core.Entity2
camzup.core.MeshEntity2
All Implemented Interfaces:
IBlenderWritable, IEntity, IOriented2, ISpatial2, ISvgWritable, IUtils, IVolume, IVolume2, Iterable<Mesh2>
Direct Known Subclasses:
ImageEntity2
public class MeshEntity2 extends Entity2 implements Iterable<Mesh2>, IVolume2, ISvgWritable, IBlenderWritable
An entity which contains a transform that is applied to a list of meshes.

    • toBlenderCode

      public String toBlenderCode(float extrude, float offset, boolean useAutoSmooth, float autoAngle, MaterialSolid[] materials, float gamma, float metallic, float roughness, float specular, float clearcoat, float clearcoatRough)
      Returns a String of Python code targeted toward the Blender 2.8x API. This code is brittle and is used for internal testing purposes, i.e., to compare how mesh geometry looks in Blender (the control) versus in the library (the test).

      the string

    • toSvgElm

      public String toSvgElm(float zoom, MaterialSolid[] materials)
      Creates a string representing a group node in the SVG format. This SVG is designed for compatibility with Processing, not for efficiency.

      Stroke weight is impacted by scaling in transforms, so zoom is a parameter. If nonuniform zooming is used, zoom can be an average of width and height or the maximum dimension.
      Parameters:
      zoom - scaling from external transforms
      materials - the materials to use
      Returns:
      the string

    • toSvgString

      public String toSvgString()
      Renders this mesh entity as an SVG string. A default material renders the mesh's fill and stroke. The background of the SVG is transparent. Sets the camera scale to 1.0.
      Specified by:
      toSvgString in interface ISvgWritable
      Returns:
      the SVG string
